detail.summary:
GLOWS will address the need for a future L-band mission to maintain data continuity at the same resolution and accuracy as the European Space Agency’s (ESA) Soil Moisture and Ocean Salinity (SMOS
) and the Soil Moisture Active Passive (SMAP
) missions.

The mission will consist of four satellites, operating in pairs, and will measure fluctuations in Earth’s gravitational field, building upon the success of similar missions such as the Gravity field and steady-state Ocean Circulation Explorer (GOCE
) mission, the Gravity Recovery and Climate Experiment (GRACE
) and its follow-on mission, GRACE-FO
.
